        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:47PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 246 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cheraw State Park, or near Cheraw, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bennettsville, Mccoll, Chavistown, Wallace, Gibson, and Tatum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
